The most recent release  (version 5.0 , July 2020) includes many relevant  novelties : (i) Coupling with the discrete el ement method   and Project Chrono ( https://projectchrono.org/ ); (ii) Coupling with  MoorDyn ( http://www.matt - hall.ca/moordyn.html ); (iii) a multi -phase solver  (soil-water and gas -liquid) ; (iv) specialised  functionality for second -order wave generation and active wave absorption, plus relaxation zones ; (v)  coupling with wave propagation models ; and (vi) inlet/outlet flow conditions.
Therefore, DualSPHysics was coupled with Mo orDyn ( http://www.matt -hall.ca/moordyn.html ), an  open -source dynamic mooring line model [88].
DualSPHysics is an open source  code available in the public repository GitHub ( https://github.com/DualSPHysics/DualSPHysics ).
